snippet.textDisplay:
Dear Daniel,

Words come short to write even...anything. Even so I want to say something so that u know that this has touched the world and many, many of us feel with u. U brother, are so strong to still give a message so that this wont repeat and nobody else will feel the pain caused to you. Brother i, and so many others cry with you right now. Im in tears. My heart is in tears. We cannot take away your pain. But I hope it will even slightly ease your tears that all over the world we cried with. May their souls rest in heaven. May u be given patience. And all others whom lost a child, be blessed and know that many others care and feel for u. U are not alone in this. The world has got your back, even if we cant bring back the precious that is lost, we are there with you. Love u brother.

snippet.textDisplay: “Towards Zero” NSW Government’s road safety slogan. How’s that working for ya, so far in 2020. “Zero Toleration” or “Zero Harm” is what is needed. High nasty  price paid in this incident. No open casket, children too disfigured and all related. Laws must be changed and even a cabinet shuffle because the government’s message is just not getting through. I am truck driver, and do try get the safety message. Alcohol does mentally impair your cognitive brain and effects, and this message needs to get out too. May God have mercy on all involved, and be safe out there on the road.
